insert into public.universities (id, country, name, verified, data) values ($sq$lmu$sq$, $sq$Germany$sq$, $sq$Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich (LMU)$sq$, false, $sq${"id":"lmu","name":"Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich (LMU)","country":"Germany","city":"Munich","flag":"🇩🇪","ranking":"Germany's highest-ranked comprehensive university","knownFor":["Medicine","Physics","Law","Psychology","Humanities"],"language":"Mostly German-taught bachelor's (TestDaF/DSH); many English-taught master's.","entryGrades":"Competitive — direct entry needs a recognised qualification (Studienkolleg year for 12-year school systems); confirm via uni-assist/anabin.","tests":"German B2/C1 for German-taught; IELTS/TOEFL for English master's — confirm per programme.","acceptance":"Competitive — varies by programme","tuitionIntl":"FREE tuition (Bavaria permits fees but LMU has not introduced general non-EU tuition — confirm current status) + semester fee ~€150. Visa needs the €11,904 blocked account (verified 2026).","living":"Munich is Germany's priciest city (~€1,200–1,500/month realistic vs the €992/month blocked-account drawdown).","deadline":"~15 July (winter semester) / ~15 January (summer) — confirm per programme.","scholarshipsHere":"Deutschlandstipendium (€300/month, nationality-blind, via the university); DAAD for graduate study. Post-study: 18-month job-seeker permit (verified).","scholarships":[],"sourceName":"LMU Munich (official)","sourceUrl":"https://www.lmu.de/en/study/","verified":false}$sq$::jsonb);
